2004-03-30 17:59  ddd

	* src/: interface/ulm_check.cc, mpi/c/mpi_test.c, mpi/c/mpi_wait.c:
	  Problem encountered in QCD burn-in code with an MPI_Irecv from
	  MPI_PROC_NULL, followed by an MPI_Test.

	  Our logic in MPI_Test for this case was wrong -- we check for a
	  valid request first, then for the placeholder proc_null request.
	  We should do it the other way around as we do for MPI_Wait.

	  Moved the check for this case into ulm_check.cc and also cleaned
	  up MPI_Test and MPI_Wait to be more symmetrical.

